Tests of electrostatic precipitators under simulated Martian conditions have achieved collection efficiencies between 94% and 99% despite voltage constraints imposed by the CO₂-rich low-pressure environment, demonstrating that electrostatic precipitation is a promising approach for effective dust removal in Martian ISRU applications.

Parameter Value
