A method using electrostatic fields has been developed to collect dust from gaseous environments at low pressures, specifically carbon dioxide at pressures around 5 to 10 mbars. The electrostatic precipitator is the best and most efficient solution for this environment; no other precipitator designs have been developed for Mars due to the challenges of the low atmospheric pressure.

